##The Tom Hanks have been diagnosed! NBA Lockout! ... First confirmed case on Capitol Hill...

With the spread of new crown pneumonia, the American people can no longer remain calm.

US President Donald Trump gave a nationally televised speech on Sunday evening, setting out the government's specific measures to deal with the new outbreak, including restricting European travel to the US and boosting the economy, foreign media reported.

Donald Trump said there would be a 30-day moratorium on "all travel from Europe to the US" from the 13th, with the exception of the UK. "The specifics will be tailored to local conditions, " he said

A total of 1,237 patients have tested positive for the new coronavirus in the United States, bringing the total to 37 deaths, the CNN reported Monday. A state of emergency has been declared in 23 states and Washington, D. C.

Tom Hanks and wife diagnosed with new coronary pneumonia

According to a CCTV news report, the actor Tom Hanks, who is in Australia, confirmed on a social networking site on the evening of November 11, US local time, he and his wife tested positive for new coronary pneumonia after experiencing cold-like fatigue, body aches and low-grade fever. The Tom Hanks said it would follow the doctor's advice to keep it up to date.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Image: Twitter

Tom Hanks is one of the most famous and accomplished actors in the world, and his Forrest Gump is widely known.

Tom Hanks was born in Concord, California, on July 9,1956. In 1993 and 1994, he starred in the Philadelphia Story and the Forrest Gump, and won two consecutive Academy Award for Best Actor.

In 1999, he appeared in the film Saving Private Ryan. In October 2001, he was awarded the Lifetime Achievement Award by the American Film Academy, and in 2020, he won the lifetime achievement award at the 77th Golden Globe Awards.

The NBA faces an indefinite lockout

The NBA will suspend games this season until further notice because of the new pneumonia outbreak, NBA officials said.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Photo: Sina Weibo

Earlier, a Utah Jazz player, Goebel, had initially tested positive for the new coronavirus. The NBA said in a statement that the player's test results were obtained before the game between the Utah Jazz and the Oklahoma City Thunder on Monday night. That night's game was canceled.

At a news conference at the Sir Tuesday game, according to media reports, Goebel ignored the epidemic and reached down to touch the microphone and recording equipment of the reporters in front of him. Now he caused this "disturbance" , but also quickly spread to the entire league, and even the United States professional arena.

##First confirmed case on Capitol Hill

US Democratic Senator Maria Cantwell said on the same night that a staff member in her office in Washington, DC, tested positive for the new coronavirus, the The Hill reported Monday.

Reported that this is the first confirmed case in the United States Congress. Cantwell has closed her office and has asked anyone who comes into contact with staff to be tested. It is alleged that those diagnosed were quarantined after symptoms developed.

Earlier, Congress began to discuss whether the Capitol should be temporarily closed. However, the speaker of the United States House of Representatives Nancy Pelosi said "members will not flee the Capitol" . Pelosi and his team have recently come under pressure to take steps to prevent a new outbreak of pneumonia in the capitol, where two thirds of senators are over 60 and the average house member is about 58. There are concerns about their health.

US SUSPENDS ALL TRAVEL TO EUROPE FOR NEXT 30 days

According to reports, Donald Trump said that affected by the epidemic, from 13 days from 30 days, will suspend "all travel from Europe to the United States, " except the United Kingdom. "The specifics will be tailored to local conditions, " he said

Donald Trump also said the parties should see this as a moment of unity and strength. "We have a common enemy, an enemy of the world, in fact, as a COVID-19, and we must defeat it as quickly and safely as possible, " he added, nothing is more important to him than the lives and safety of the American people.

Washington has declared a state of emergency

A state of emergency was declared in Washington, D. C. , on the afternoon of March 11, as a new outbreak of pneumonia intensified. Health officials in Washington, D.C. , say there are now 10 confirmed cases of the disease in the region, and more cases are expected to follow.

Washington, DC Mayor Bowser said the declaration of a state of emergency would allow the capital region to use more resources to deal with the outbreak, local health authorities have also recommended the postponement or cancellation of non-essential mass public events for more than 1,000 people. Universities in and around Washington, including the University of Virginia, the Georgetown University, the Howard University and the Catholic University of the United States, have also announced they will suspend classes, The Washington Post reported, most schools will switch to online teaching.

A state of emergency has been declared in 24 states and the capital, Washington, D.C. , as new crown disease continues to spread across the United States, according to the CNN. A state of emergency is in place to allow states to urgently mobilize resources to respond to the outbreak. A state of emergency has been declared in Arizona, New Mexico, Louisiana, Arkansas and Washington, D. C.

In addition, at the hearing held by the United States House of Representatives on the 11th, in response to the serious shortage of new coronavirus testing reagents in the United States, the director of the US Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) responded to a question from a member of Congress: "Are there cases in the United States that are currently thought to have died from influenza that may actually have died from a new coronavirus infection? " There have been cases of death from a new coronavirus that was originally diagnosed as having the flu.

#Stocks Tumble again as Dow enters technical bear market

#

As the global panic over the new crown continues to spread, financial markets continue their roller coaster ride, with Tuesday tumbling after black Monday, only to be pummeled again on Wednesday, the U. S. stock market is a "one-night Bungee" straight into the technical bear market. Many Chinese and foreign institutions believe the 11-year bull market in US stocks may be coming to an end.

U.S. stocks fell again on Wednesday as they opened lower. The Dow went into a technical bear market at 1,464.94. By the close, the Dow was down 1,464.94, or 5.86 percent, at 23,553.22; the Nasdaq was down 392.20, or 4.70 percent, at 7,952.05; and the S & P 500 was down 140.85, or 4.89 percent, at 2,741.38.

With the dow down 17.47% since 2020 as of March 11, and a 20% drop from its February 12 peak, the Dow is in a technical bear market. WHY HAVEN'T U.S. stocks bottomed out?

According to US media reports, the stock market's performance on the day suggested that investors believe the US government has not done enough to deal with the impact of the new pneumonia outbreak, both on itself and on the economy.

Analysts say it is impossible to predict the duration and extent of the new pneumonia outbreak, and the resulting uncertainty will continue to destabilize financial markets.
